    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has begun to soften, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> with the <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>ground coriander</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong> and <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) – this is your <strong>fajita spice base</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 1 min or until the garlic has slightly softened</p><p>Add the<strong> halved cherry tomatoes</strong> and <strong>sliced pepper</strong> with a small splash of <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until the tomatoes begin to blister</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
